{{Top|rwp}}
'''Dermot Power''' is an illustrator, comic book artist, and concept artist who worked on ''[[Star Wars]]'' films such as [[Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones|''Attack of the Clones'']] and [[Star Wars: Episode VII The Force Awakens|''The Force Awakens'']]. He started as a children's books artist.

Some of his unused early concept artwork for the ''Attack of the Clones'' [[Sith Lord/Legends|Sith Lord]] was later used to become [[Asajj Ventress/Legends|Asajj Ventress]] in ''[[Star Wars: Clone Wars]]'' and other works.

In the [[2015]] reference book ''[[The Art of Star Wars: The Force Awakens]]'', Power's concept work on a chrome [[First Order stormtrooper|stormtrooper]] is featured, a character which eventually became [[Captain]] [[Phasma]] in ''The Force Awakens'' film.

